form_title.ms_form_title_llm_v1: Excerpt of the Registry of Birth Certificates for the commune of Cap-Haien

full_text: Screened by NARA, 7/31/2023 LIBERTY EQUALITY FRATERNITY REPUBLIC OF HAITI Excerpt of the Registry of Birth Certificates for the commune of Cap-Haitien deposed at the National Archives of the Republic A2 No. 89460 In the year nineteen hundred and seven, the 104th of our YEAR - 1907 Independence and on Thursday October twenty fourth at ten PAGE - 74 o'clock in the morning. Before me, Ovide Lescot, NUMBER 289 undersigned, Civil Registrar of Cap-Haitien; Appeared Mr. Antonio Schettini, merchant residing in Cap-Haitien Who brought forth a female child whom he declared to be his daughter, born in this town on October sixteen of the current year at nine thirty in the morning from Julia Scianciolli, also merchant residing in the same town, To BIRTH CERTIFI- which child, he has given the first names of: CATE OF: PHILOMENE ELVIRA PHILOMENE This act was drawn up in the presence of Denor Joseph, ELVIRA shoemaker and Arthur Brown, salesman, both residing and SCHETTINI, domiciled in the above-mentionned town. After reading the born on present act, we have signed it with the parties. October 16, 1907, 104th SIGNED: OVIDE LESCOT. year of the Port-au-Prince, this 8th day of March 1990. Independance Certified true copy Collationned. ANHA/ 422733 JEAN WILFRID BERTRAND GENERAL DIRECTOR Only for the legalization of the signature of M. Jean Wilfrid BERTRAND General Director of the National Archives Receipt No. 65232HH Public Prosecutor's office, this 15th day of March 1990. Me. Arthur Gerard Delbeau, lawyer Commissioner for the Government I, Martine Joseph, certify this to be a correct translation of the original document in French, to the best of my understanding and belief.
